cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is about a dataset of novel English words published in the New York Times, which is relevant to natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics (CL). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses baseline results for both uncontextual and contextual prediction of novelty class, which involves machine learning and could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions manually annotating the dataset, which could relate to information retrieval (cs.IR) or neural networks (cs.NE).
